title: Drawing, "Foliate Design"
description: The foliate design, in green, is comprised of various foliate forms: a central curved stem that branches off into left and right curves; two sets of tripartite leaves attached to the main stem also branching off on both sides; and a pair of shell-like forms splitting off from a curved stem attached to the lower part of the central one.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Foliate Design".
28 x 21.5 cm (11 x 8 1/2 in.). Gift of Ellen Gustav Jensen. 1956-47-16.
